r.com/ez1Cjif.png\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAnd mini jet...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/CKHSNE1.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://i.imgur.com/CKHSNE1.png\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThanks! I really like the seated mini plane, so cute!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"problemecium","CreatedById":101649,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-31T00:01:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027ve recently reworked my Stackable Ion Probe:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/tMBhJAw\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/tMBhJAw.png\u0022 alt=\u0022tMBhJAw.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnfortunately, due to the probe core rebalance that came in 0.90 (I think), it\u0027s stuck using the fat OKTO rather than the OKTO2, with which I could have made it smaller than a Kerbal. At present, it\u0027s the diameter of a Kerbal and the height of a Mk1 pod.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhy so many sensors? It\u0027s designed to enter orbit around a planet or moon and strip mine all biomes as best as can be done from space; there is an antenna for transmissions, but sponging up the remaining Science requires recovering at least two temperature scans and three gravioli scans per biome, so I\u0027ve included twelve to enable full scans of up to four biomes per flight.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-05-31T00:07:01Z\u0022 title=\u002205/31/2015 12:07  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EMay 31, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by parameciumkid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lime","CreatedById":137978,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-06T11:31:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ELittle Joe II Replica\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/OV11om8.png\u0022 alt=\u0022OV11om8.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Overland","CreatedById":119812,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-06T12:10:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Ehmmm.. I did have a tiny yard-flea shunter in an earlier save.. but 3701 being an industrial type branch line locomotive would qualify.. shes much smaller than any mainline train.. as are her wagons \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E still doesnt quite fit in a car space though\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/E7xEZ4K.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022E7xEZ4K.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Whippler","CreatedById":143730,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-06T16:31:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMy little rescue/debris cleaner probe being launched to low Kerbin orbit!\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://puu.sh/ieIiF/766496eb75.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022766496eb75.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"hellblazer","CreatedById":131384,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-06T19:53:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/a93NoJ0.png\u0022 alt=\u0022a93NoJ0.png\u0022\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mike9606","CreatedById":90275,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-06T20:01:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Overland\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Overland\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003Ehmmm.. I did have a tiny yard-flea shunter in an earlier save.. but 3701 being an industrial type branch line locomotive would qualify.. shes much smaller than any mainline train.. as are her wagons \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E still doesnt quite fit in a car space though\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/E7xEZ4K.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://i.imgur.com/E7xEZ4K.jpg\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI assume the wheels are done via kerbpaint, but how do you do the numbers on the side?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Overland","CreatedById":119812,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-07T00:23:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThe flag is a custom alpha texture that I overwrote one of the ugly stock flags with.. so that all that show are the numbers themselves and no background.. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ehappily when planting a flag externally KSP automaticly puts a white background\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ethe mod im using is called flag decals \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.curse.com/ksp-mods/kerbal/222813-flag-decals-v2-3\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.curse.com/ksp-mods/kerbal/222813-flag-decals-v2-3\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Eit lets you place the mission flag in an assortment of ways on craft using its own 3d modeled paper thin part.. more like a sticker..\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ethey come in curved, straight.. large, small etc.. a very useful mod to have \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ethe painted rover wheels are a seperate custom mod from the stock ones I created.. but you can just as simply repaint the existing stock ones, I used GIMP on linux with the DDS plugin to invert the colour, change to black.. enhance it a little.. and in the case of the locomotive drive wheels on the center 4 of 3701 I highlighted a few sections and turned their respective colours white.. the effect is rather nice..\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EJust make sure you save with the DX whatever it is 1 compression when saving..\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EKerbpaint, never heard of it but I think i\u0027ll have to look into it, thanks\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI might be using linux now but I used windows before. the procedure is the same with no difference.. have fun \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-06-07T00:29:00Z\u0022 title=\u002206/07/2015 12:29  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EJune 7, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by Overland\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EthanSchlegel","CreatedById":114346,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-07T01:50:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Whippler\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Whippler\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMy little rescue/debris cleaner probe being launched to low Kerbin orbit!\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://puu.sh/ieIiF/766496eb75.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://puu.sh/ieIiF/766496eb75.jpg\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EReminds me of my mini debris clearing satellite \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/97002-Batwing-SSTO-%28FAR%29?highlight=Batwing\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/97002-Batwing-SSTO-%28FAR%29?highlight=Batwing\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"eorin","CreatedById":79133,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-08T12:29:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Emy little mini millennium falcon\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/seMdMZI.png\u0022 alt=\u0022seMdMZI.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gmiddlemass","CreatedById":111037,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-08T14:19:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThat Millennium Falcon looks great \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JTMilne","CreatedById":113192,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-09T01:33:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EA little truck I made \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022640\u0022 height=\u0022480\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dr Farnsworth","CreatedById":147177,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-28T17:03:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EGood news everyone!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECan\u0027t afford a landing craft with all the amenities, such as, a capsule, lights, oxidizer? Well have we got the craft for you!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe Farnsworth design team found some old lawn chairs and left over fuel cans, and whala! The Farnsworth Bumblebee!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETesting is still being performed on the craft, err, eva chair, um, fueled lawn chair. so far most of the pilots have survived.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/iL53fRp.png\u0022 alt=\u0022iL53fRp.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/L6GICLf.png\u0022 alt=\u0022L6GICLf.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022//imgur.com/a/Mxlgd\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EJavascript is disabled. View full album\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe Bumblebee can be found on KerbalX through my sig.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ADK","CreatedById":147710,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-28T17:45:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI love the Bumblebee \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"clivman","CreatedById":139191,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-29T02:00:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EDoes Sojourner count as a mini-craft?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"problemecium","CreatedById":101649,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-29T05:07:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWIP: a spaceplane for Laythe that can fit into a Mk3 cargo bay. It can almost SSTO on Kerbin, so it \u003Cem\u003Eshould\u003C/em\u003E be able to SSTO on Laythe, but I haven\u0027t checked yet.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/qy0YYQR\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/qy0YYQR.png\u0022 alt=\u0022qy0YYQR.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lime","CreatedById":137978,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-29T06:26:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022clivman\u0022 data-cite=\u0022clivman\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EDoes Sojourner count as a mini-craft?\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E Yes it does.\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\n"}]}